Classify the issue type and use the corresponding template to generate the product specification.

## Decision Table

|Type|Question|Signal Words|Template|
|----|--------|------------|--------|
|`feature`|Does it add new functionality?|"add", "create", "new", "implement", "build"|`reference/feature.md`|
|`bug`|Does it fix something broken?|"error", "fail", "broken", "doesn't work", "bug"|`reference/bug.md`|
|`chore`|Is it maintenance or config?|"update", "configure", "migrate", "dependencies", "upgrade"|`reference/chore.md`|
|`refactor`|Does it improve code without changing behavior?|"clean", "reorganize", "improve code", "restructure"|`reference/refactor.md`|
|`perf`|Does it improve performance?|"slow", "optimize", "performance", "speed up"|`reference/perf.md`|
